India May Boost Wheat, Rice Production in 2011, USDA Unit Says

-- B y   W h i t n e y   M c F e r r o n
-- 
2011-03-02T20:08:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/india-may-boost-wheat-rice-production-in-2011-usda-unit-says.html
  India  may produce 83 million metric
tons of wheat in the year that will begin April 1, up from 80.8
million this year, a unit of the U.S. Department of Agriculture
said in a  report  posted today on its website.  India’s rough-rice production may increase to 147.015
million tons in the year that will begin Oct. 1, up from 141.764
million tons this year and 133.648 million last year, the USDA’s
Foreign Agricultural Service said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Whitney McFerron in  Chicago  at 
 wmcferron1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net . 